Isle is a computer&hellip; (common intro). In this post I discuss the Isle design and why I made these choices. I aimed to keep everything as simple as possible, while supporting a wide-range of applications.
Following this post will be monthly Isle updates&hellip;
CPU Simple 32-bit RISC-V processor runs system and controls other hardware. Performance is broadly comparable with a 486 or Motorola 68040, thought our CPU doesn&rsquo;t have hardware floating point.
